23using H264::kAud;
24using H264::kSps;

29const char kAnnexBHeaderBytes[4] = {0, 0, 0, 1};
30const size_t kAvccHeaderByteSize = sizeof(uint32_t);
31
32bool H264CMSampleBufferToAnnexBBuffer(CMSampleBufferRef avcc_sample_buffer,
33 bool is_keyframe,
34 rtc::Buffer* annexb_buffer) {
35 RTC_DCHECK(avcc_sample_buffer);
36
37 // Get format description from the sample buffer.
38 CMVideoFormatDescriptionRef description =
39 CMSampleBufferGetFormatDescription(avcc_sample_buffer);
40 if (description == nullptr) {
41 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to get sample buffer's description.";
42 return false;
43 }
44
45 // Get parameter set information.
46 int nalu_header_size = 0;
47 size_t param_set_count = 0;
48 OSStatus status = CMVideoFormatDescriptionGetH264ParameterSetAtIndex(
49 description, 0, nullptr, nullptr, &param_set_count, &nalu_header_size);
50 if (status != noErr) {
51 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to get parameter set.";
52 return false;
53 }
54 RTC_CHECK_EQ(nalu_header_size, kAvccHeaderByteSize);
55 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(param_set_count, 2);
56
57 // Truncate any previous data in the buffer without changing its capacity.
58 annexb_buffer->SetSize(0);
59
60 // Place all parameter sets at the front of buffer.
61 if (is_keyframe) {
62 size_t param_set_size = 0;
63 const uint8_t* param_set = nullptr;
64 for (size_t i = 0; i < param_set_count; ++i) {
65 status = CMVideoFormatDescriptionGetH264ParameterSetAtIndex(
66 description, i, &param_set, &param_set_size, nullptr, nullptr);
67 if (status != noErr) {
68 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to get parameter set.";
69 return false;
70 }
71 // Update buffer.
72 annexb_buffer->AppendData(kAnnexBHeaderBytes, sizeof(kAnnexBHeaderBytes));
73 annexb_buffer->AppendData(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(param_set),
74 param_set_size);
75 }
76 }
77
78 // Get block buffer from the sample buffer.
79 CMBlockBufferRef block_buffer =
80 CMSampleBufferGetDataBuffer(avcc_sample_buffer);
81 if (block_buffer == nullptr) {
82 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to get sample buffer's block buffer.";
83 return false;
84 }
85 CMBlockBufferRef contiguous_buffer = nullptr;
86 // Make sure block buffer is contiguous.
87 if (!CMBlockBufferIsRangeContiguous(block_buffer, 0, 0)) {
88 status = CMBlockBufferCreateContiguous(
89 nullptr, block_buffer, nullptr, nullptr, 0, 0, 0, &contiguous_buffer);
90 if (status != noErr) {
91 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to flatten non-contiguous block buffer: "
92 << status;
93 return false;
94 }
95 } else {
96 contiguous_buffer = block_buffer;
97 // Retain to make cleanup easier.
98 CFRetain(contiguous_buffer);
99 block_buffer = nullptr;
100 }
101
102 // Now copy the actual data.
103 char* data_ptr = nullptr;
104 size_t block_buffer_size = CMBlockBufferGetDataLength(contiguous_buffer);
105 status = CMBlockBufferGetDataPointer(contiguous_buffer, 0, nullptr, nullptr,
106 &data_ptr);
107 if (status != noErr) {
108 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to get block buffer data.";
109 CFRelease(contiguous_buffer);
110 return false;
111 }
112 size_t bytes_remaining = block_buffer_size;
113 while (bytes_remaining > 0) {
114 // The size type here must match |nalu_header_size|, we expect 4 bytes.
115 // Read the length of the next packet of data. Must convert from big endian
116 // to host endian.
117 RTC_DCHECK_GE(bytes_remaining, (size_t)nalu_header_size);
118 uint32_t* uint32_data_ptr = reinterpret_cast<uint32_t*>(data_ptr);
119 uint32_t packet_size = CFSwapInt32BigToHost(*uint32_data_ptr);
120 // Update buffer.
121 annexb_buffer->AppendData(kAnnexBHeaderBytes, sizeof(kAnnexBHeaderBytes));
122 annexb_buffer->AppendData(data_ptr + nalu_header_size, packet_size);
123
124 size_t bytes_written = packet_size + sizeof(kAnnexBHeaderBytes);
125 bytes_remaining -= bytes_written;
126 data_ptr += bytes_written;
127 }
128 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(bytes_remaining, (size_t)0);
129
130 CFRelease(contiguous_buffer);
131 return true;
132}
133
134bool H264AnnexBBufferToCMSampleBuffer(const uint8_t* annexb_buffer,
135 size_t annexb_buffer_size,
136 CMVideoFormatDescriptionRef video_format,
137 CMSampleBufferRef* out_sample_buffer,
138 CMMemoryPoolRef memory_pool) {
139 RTC_DCHECK(annexb_buffer);
140 RTC_DCHECK(out_sample_buffer);
141 RTC_DCHECK(video_format);
142 *out_sample_buffer = nullptr;
143
144 AnnexBBufferReader reader(annexb_buffer, annexb_buffer_size);
145 if (reader.SeekToNextNaluOfType(kSps)) {
146 // Buffer contains an SPS NALU - skip it and the following PPS
147 const uint8_t* data;
148 size_t data_len;
149 if (!reader.ReadNalu(&data, &data_len)) {
150 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to read SPS";
151 return false;
152 }
153 if (!reader.ReadNalu(&data, &data_len)) {
154 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to read PPS";
155 return false;
156 }
157 } else {
158 // No SPS NALU - start reading from the first NALU in the buffer
159 reader.SeekToStart();
160 }
161
162 // Allocate memory as a block buffer.
163 CMBlockBufferRef block_buffer = nullptr;
164 CFAllocatorRef block_allocator = CMMemoryPoolGetAllocator(memory_pool);
165 OSStatus status = CMBlockBufferCreateWithMemoryBlock(
166 kCFAllocatorDefault, nullptr, reader.BytesRemaining(), block_allocator,
167 nullptr, 0, reader.BytesRemaining(), kCMBlockBufferAssureMemoryNowFlag,
168 &block_buffer);
169 if (status != kCMBlockBufferNoErr) {
170 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to create block buffer.";
171 return false;
172 }
173
174 // Make sure block buffer is contiguous.
175 CMBlockBufferRef contiguous_buffer = nullptr;
176 if (!CMBlockBufferIsRangeContiguous(block_buffer, 0, 0)) {
177 status = CMBlockBufferCreateContiguous(kCFAllocatorDefault, block_buffer,
178 block_allocator, nullptr, 0, 0, 0,
179 &contiguous_buffer);
180 if (status != noErr) {
181 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to flatten non-contiguous block buffer: "
182 << status;
183 CFRelease(block_buffer);
184 return false;
185 }
186 } else {
187 contiguous_buffer = block_buffer;
188 block_buffer = nullptr;
189 }
190
191 // Get a raw pointer into allocated memory.
192 size_t block_buffer_size = 0;
193 char* data_ptr = nullptr;
194 status = CMBlockBufferGetDataPointer(contiguous_buffer, 0, nullptr,
195 &block_buffer_size, &data_ptr);
196 if (status != kCMBlockBufferNoErr) {
197 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to get block buffer data pointer.";
198 CFRelease(contiguous_buffer);
199 return false;
200 }
201 RTC_DCHECK(block_buffer_size == reader.BytesRemaining());
202
203 // Write Avcc NALUs into block buffer memory.
204 AvccBufferWriter writer(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(data_ptr),
205 block_buffer_size);
206 while (reader.BytesRemaining() > 0) {
207 const uint8_t* nalu_data_ptr = nullptr;
208 size_t nalu_data_size = 0;
209 if (reader.ReadNalu(&nalu_data_ptr, &nalu_data_size)) {
210 writer.WriteNalu(nalu_data_ptr, nalu_data_size);
211 }
212 }
213
214 // Create sample buffer.
215 status = CMSampleBufferCreate(kCFAllocatorDefault, contiguous_buffer, true,
216 nullptr, nullptr, video_format, 1, 0, nullptr,
217 0, nullptr, out_sample_buffer);
218 if (status != noErr) {
219 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to create sample buffer.";
220 CFRelease(contiguous_buffer);
221 return false;
222 }
223 CFRelease(contiguous_buffer);
224 return true;
225}

227#ifndef DISABLE_H265
228bool H265CMSampleBufferToAnnexBBuffer(
229 CMSampleBufferRef hvcc_sample_buffer,
230 bool is_keyframe,
231 rtc::Buffer* annexb_buffer) {
232 RTC_DCHECK(hvcc_sample_buffer);
233
234 // Get format description from the sample buffer.
235 CMVideoFormatDescriptionRef description =
236 CMSampleBufferGetFormatDescription(hvcc_sample_buffer);
237 if (description == nullptr) {
238 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to get sample buffer's description.";
239 return false;
240 }
241
242 // Get parameter set information.
243 int nalu_header_size = 0;
244 size_t param_set_count = 0;
245 OSStatus status = CMVideoFormatDescriptionGetHEVCParameterSetAtIndex(
246 description, 0, nullptr, nullptr, &param_set_count, &nalu_header_size);
247 if (status != noErr) {
248 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to get parameter set.";
249 return false;
250 }
251 RTC_CHECK_EQ(nalu_header_size, kAvccHeaderByteSize);
252 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(param_set_count, 3);
253
254 // Truncate any previous data in the buffer without changing its capacity.
255 annexb_buffer->SetSize(0);
256
257 size_t nalu_offset = 0;
258 std::vector<size_t> frag_offsets;
259 std::vector<size_t> frag_lengths;
260
261 // Place all parameter sets at the front of buffer.
262 if (is_keyframe) {
263 size_t param_set_size = 0;
264 const uint8_t* param_set = nullptr;
265 for (size_t i = 0; i < param_set_count; ++i) {
266 status = CMVideoFormatDescriptionGetHEVCParameterSetAtIndex(
267 description, i, &param_set, &param_set_size, nullptr, nullptr);
268 if (status != noErr) {
269 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to get parameter set.";
270 return false;
271 }
272 // Update buffer.
273 annexb_buffer->AppendData(kAnnexBHeaderBytes, sizeof(kAnnexBHeaderBytes));
274 annexb_buffer->AppendData(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(param_set),
275 param_set_size);
276 // Update fragmentation.
277 frag_offsets.push_back(nalu_offset + sizeof(kAnnexBHeaderBytes));
278 frag_lengths.push_back(param_set_size);
279 nalu_offset += sizeof(kAnnexBHeaderBytes) + param_set_size;
280 }
281 }
282
283 // Get block buffer from the sample buffer.
284 CMBlockBufferRef block_buffer =
285 CMSampleBufferGetDataBuffer(hvcc_sample_buffer);
286 if (block_buffer == nullptr) {
287 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to get sample buffer's block buffer.";
288 return false;
289 }
290 CMBlockBufferRef contiguous_buffer = nullptr;
291 // Make sure block buffer is contiguous.
292 if (!CMBlockBufferIsRangeContiguous(block_buffer, 0, 0)) {
293 status = CMBlockBufferCreateContiguous(
294 nullptr, block_buffer, nullptr, nullptr, 0, 0, 0, &contiguous_buffer);
295 if (status != noErr) {
296 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to flatten non-contiguous block buffer: "
297 << status;
298 return false;
299 }
300 } else {
301 contiguous_buffer = block_buffer;
302 // Retain to make cleanup easier.
303 CFRetain(contiguous_buffer);
304 block_buffer = nullptr;
305 }
306
307 // Now copy the actual data.
308 char* data_ptr = nullptr;
309 size_t block_buffer_size = CMBlockBufferGetDataLength(contiguous_buffer);
310 status = CMBlockBufferGetDataPointer(contiguous_buffer, 0, nullptr, nullptr,
311 &data_ptr);
312 if (status != noErr) {
313 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to get block buffer data.";
314 CFRelease(contiguous_buffer);
315 return false;
316 }
317 size_t bytes_remaining = block_buffer_size;
318 while (bytes_remaining > 0) {
319 // The size type here must match |nalu_header_size|, we expect 4 bytes.
320 // Read the length of the next packet of data. Must convert from big endian
321 // to host endian.
322 RTC_DCHECK_GE(bytes_remaining, (size_t)nalu_header_size);
323 uint32_t* uint32_data_ptr = reinterpret_cast<uint32_t*>(data_ptr);
324 uint32_t packet_size = CFSwapInt32BigToHost(*uint32_data_ptr);
325 // Update buffer.
326 annexb_buffer->AppendData(kAnnexBHeaderBytes, sizeof(kAnnexBHeaderBytes));
327 annexb_buffer->AppendData(data_ptr + nalu_header_size, packet_size);
328 // Update fragmentation.
329 frag_offsets.push_back(nalu_offset + sizeof(kAnnexBHeaderBytes));
330 frag_lengths.push_back(packet_size);
331 nalu_offset += sizeof(kAnnexBHeaderBytes) + packet_size;
332
333 size_t bytes_written = packet_size + sizeof(kAnnexBHeaderBytes);
334 bytes_remaining -= bytes_written;
335 data_ptr += bytes_written;
336 }
337 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(bytes_remaining, (size_t)0);
338
339 CFRelease(contiguous_buffer);
340
341 return true;
342}

344bool H265AnnexBBufferToCMSampleBuffer(const uint8_t* annexb_buffer,
345 size_t annexb_buffer_size,
346 CMVideoFormatDescriptionRef video_format,
347 CMSampleBufferRef* out_sample_buffer) {
348 RTC_DCHECK(annexb_buffer);
349 RTC_DCHECK(out_sample_buffer);
350 RTC_DCHECK(video_format);
351 *out_sample_buffer = nullptr;
352
353 AnnexBBufferReader reader(annexb_buffer, annexb_buffer_size, false);
354 if (reader.SeekToNextNaluOfType(H265::kVps)) {
355 // Buffer contains an SPS NALU - skip it and the following PPS
356 const uint8_t* data;
357 size_t data_len;
358 if (!reader.ReadNalu(&data, &data_len)) {
359 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to read VPS";
360 return false;
361 }
362 if (!reader.ReadNalu(&data, &data_len)) {
363 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to read SPS";
364 return false;
365 }
366 if (!reader.ReadNalu(&data, &data_len)) {
367 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to read PPS";
368 return false;
369 }
370 } else {
371 // No SPS NALU - start reading from the first NALU in the buffer
372 reader.SeekToStart();
373 }
374
375 // Allocate memory as a block buffer.
376 // TODO(tkchin): figure out how to use a pool.
377 CMBlockBufferRef block_buffer = nullptr;
378 OSStatus status = CMBlockBufferCreateWithMemoryBlock(
379 nullptr, nullptr, reader.BytesRemaining(), nullptr, nullptr, 0,
380 reader.BytesRemaining(), kCMBlockBufferAssureMemoryNowFlag,
381 &block_buffer);
382 if (status != kCMBlockBufferNoErr) {
383 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to create block buffer.";
384 return false;
385 }
386
387 // Make sure block buffer is contiguous.
388 CMBlockBufferRef contiguous_buffer = nullptr;
389 if (!CMBlockBufferIsRangeContiguous(block_buffer, 0, 0)) {
390 status = CMBlockBufferCreateContiguous(
391 nullptr, block_buffer, nullptr, nullptr, 0, 0, 0, &contiguous_buffer);
392 if (status != noErr) {
393 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to flatten non-contiguous block buffer: "
394 << status;
395 CFRelease(block_buffer);
396 return false;
397 }
398 } else {
399 contiguous_buffer = block_buffer;
400 block_buffer = nullptr;
401 }
402
403 // Get a raw pointer into allocated memory.
404 size_t block_buffer_size = 0;
405 char* data_ptr = nullptr;
406 status = CMBlockBufferGetDataPointer(contiguous_buffer, 0, nullptr,
407 &block_buffer_size, &data_ptr);
408 if (status != kCMBlockBufferNoErr) {
409 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to get block buffer data pointer.";
410 CFRelease(contiguous_buffer);
411 return false;
412 }
413 RTC_DCHECK(block_buffer_size == reader.BytesRemaining());
414
415 // Write Avcc NALUs into block buffer memory.
416 AvccBufferWriter writer(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(data_ptr),
417 block_buffer_size);
418 while (reader.BytesRemaining() > 0) {
419 const uint8_t* nalu_data_ptr = nullptr;
420 size_t nalu_data_size = 0;
421 if (reader.ReadNalu(&nalu_data_ptr, &nalu_data_size)) {
422 writer.WriteNalu(nalu_data_ptr, nalu_data_size);
423 }
424 }
425
426 // Create sample buffer.
427 status = CMSampleBufferCreate(nullptr, contiguous_buffer, true, nullptr,
428 nullptr, video_format, 1, 0, nullptr, 0,
429 nullptr, out_sample_buffer);
430 if (status != noErr) {
431 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to create sample buffer.";
432 CFRelease(contiguous_buffer);
433 return false;
434 }
435 CFRelease(contiguous_buffer);
436 return true;
437}
438#endif

440CMVideoFormatDescriptionRef CreateVideoFormatDescription(
441 const uint8_t* annexb_buffer,
442 size_t annexb_buffer_size) {
443 const uint8_t* param_set_ptrs[2] = {};
444 size_t param_set_sizes[2] = {};
445 AnnexBBufferReader reader(annexb_buffer, annexb_buffer_size);
446 // Skip everyting before the SPS, then read the SPS and PPS
447 if (!reader.SeekToNextNaluOfType(kSps)) {
448 return nullptr;
449 }
450 if (!reader.ReadNalu(&param_set_ptrs[0], &param_set_sizes[0])) {
451 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to read SPS";
452 return nullptr;
453 }
454 if (!reader.ReadNalu(&param_set_ptrs[1], &param_set_sizes[1])) {
455 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to read PPS";
456 return nullptr;
457 }
458
459 // Parse the SPS and PPS into a CMVideoFormatDescription.
460 CMVideoFormatDescriptionRef description = nullptr;
461 OSStatus status = CMVideoFormatDescriptionCreateFromH264ParameterSets(
462 kCFAllocatorDefault, 2, param_set_ptrs, param_set_sizes, 4, &description);
463 if (status != noErr) {
464 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to create video format description.";
465 return nullptr;
466 }
467 return description;
468}

470#ifndef DISABLE_H265
471CMVideoFormatDescriptionRef CreateH265VideoFormatDescription(
472 const uint8_t* annexb_buffer,
473 size_t annexb_buffer_size) {
474 const uint8_t* param_set_ptrs[3] = {};
475 size_t param_set_sizes[3] = {};
476 AnnexBBufferReader reader(annexb_buffer, annexb_buffer_size, false);
477 // Skip everyting before the VPS, then read the VPS, SPS and PPS
478 if (!reader.SeekToNextNaluOfType(H265::kVps)) {
479 return nullptr;
480 }
481 if (!reader.ReadNalu(&param_set_ptrs[0], &param_set_sizes[0])) {
482 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to read VPS";
483 return nullptr;
484 }
485 if (!reader.ReadNalu(&param_set_ptrs[1], &param_set_sizes[1])) {
486 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to read SPS";
487 return nullptr;
488 }
489 if (!reader.ReadNalu(&param_set_ptrs[2], &param_set_sizes[2])) {
490 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to read PPS";
491 return nullptr;
492 }
493
494 // Parse the SPS and PPS into a CMVideoFormatDescription.
495 CMVideoFormatDescriptionRef description = nullptr;
496 OSStatus status = CMVideoFormatDescriptionCreateFromHEVCParameterSets(
497 kCFAllocatorDefault, 3, param_set_ptrs, param_set_sizes, 4, nullptr,
498 &description);
499 if (status != noErr) {
500 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to create video format description.";
501 return nullptr;
502 }
503 return description;
504}
505#endif

507AnnexBBufferReader::AnnexBBufferReader(const uint8_t* annexb_buffer,
508 size_t length, bool isH264)
509 : start_(annexb_buffer), length_(length) {
510 RTC_DCHECK(annexb_buffer);
511
512 offsets_ = isH264 ? H264::FindNaluIndices(annexb_buffer, length) : H265::FindNaluIndices(annexb_buffer, length);
513 offset_ = offsets_.begin();
514}
515
516AnnexBBufferReader::~AnnexBBufferReader() = default;
517
518bool AnnexBBufferReader::ReadNalu(const uint8_t** out_nalu,
519 size_t* out_length) {
520 RTC_DCHECK(out_nalu);
521 RTC_DCHECK(out_length);
522 *out_nalu = nullptr;
523 *out_length = 0;
524
525 if (offset_ == offsets_.end()) {
526 return false;
527 }
528 *out_nalu = start_ + offset_->payload_start_offset;
529 *out_length = offset_->payload_size;
530 ++offset_;
531 return true;
532}
533
534size_t AnnexBBufferReader::BytesRemaining() const {
535 if (offset_ == offsets_.end()) {
536 return 0;
537 }
538 return length_ - offset_->start_offset;
539}
540
541void AnnexBBufferReader::SeekToStart() {
542 offset_ = offsets_.begin();
543}
544
545bool AnnexBBufferReader::SeekToNextNaluOfType(NaluType type) {
546 for (; offset_ != offsets_.end(); ++offset_) {
547 if (offset_->payload_size < 1)
548 continue;
549 if (ParseNaluType(*(start_ + offset_->payload_start_offset)) == type)
550 return true;
551 }
552 return false;
553}
554
555#ifndef DISABLE_H265
556bool AnnexBBufferReader::SeekToNextNaluOfType(H265::NaluType type) {
557 for (; offset_ != offsets_.end(); ++offset_) {
558 if (offset_->payload_size < 1)
559 continue;
560 if (H265::ParseNaluType(*(start_ + offset_->payload_start_offset)) == type)
561 return true;
562 }
563 return false;
564}
565#endif
566
567AvccBufferWriter::AvccBufferWriter(uint8_t* const avcc_buffer, size_t length)
568 : start_(avcc_buffer), offset_(0), length_(length) {
569 RTC_DCHECK(avcc_buffer);
570}
571
572bool AvccBufferWriter::WriteNalu(const uint8_t* data, size_t data_size) {
573 // Check if we can write this length of data.
574 if (data_size + kAvccHeaderByteSize > BytesRemaining()) {
575 return false;
576 }
577 // Write length header, which needs to be big endian.
578 uint32_t big_endian_length = CFSwapInt32HostToBig(data_size);
579 memcpy(start_ + offset_, &big_endian_length, sizeof(big_endian_length));
580 offset_ += sizeof(big_endian_length);
581 // Write data.
582 memcpy(start_ + offset_, data, data_size);
583 offset_ += data_size;
584 return true;
585}
586
587size_t AvccBufferWriter::BytesRemaining() const {
588 return length_ - offset_;
589}
